          <p class="text-[17px] leading-relaxed text-gray-800 mb-4">Once the removal team has left, check these straight away. For the full week-by-week breakdown, see our <a href="/moving-house-checklist/" class="text-primary-600 underline hover:text-primary-700">moving house checklist</a>.</p>

          <ul class="space-y-3 text-[17px] leading-relaxed text-gray-800 mb-4">
            <li><strong>Meter readings:</strong> Take readings for gas, electric, and water immediately. Photograph each meter.</li>
            <li><strong>Stopcock and fuse box:</strong> Locate both before you need them.</li>
            <li><strong>Locks:</strong> Consider changing them &mdash; you don&rsquo;t know how many key copies exist.</li>
            <li><strong>Smoke and CO alarms:</strong> Test every one. Replace if older than 10 years.</li>
            <li><strong>Boiler service:</strong> Book one within the first few weeks if you don&rsquo;t have a recent gas safety certificate.</li>
            <li><strong>Register with local services:</strong> GP, dentist, optician, electoral roll &mdash; do this in your first week.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

